Bottom line: the deliberate fracture thesis is plausible but currently over-claimed. The data more strongly supports “calibrated economic coercion against the UAE as the Gulf’s most leverage-rich commercial node” than “Iran is specifically trying to provoke an isolated UAE military response to split the GCC.”

